BATHING IN THIS MOMENT. (gasps)

11:42.072 --> 11:43.373
OH, GOSH.

11:43.373 --> 11:46.136
IT FEELS SO GOOD ON MY SKIN.

11:49.409 --> 11:51.411
AH,
NOTHING WE CAN DO TONIGHT.

11:51.411 --> 11:53.413
WE'LL BED DOWN HERE,
THEN AT FIRST LIGHT,

11:53.413 --> 11:55.485
WE GRAB HARD HATS,
A COUPLE OF MUSTACHES,

11:55.485 --> 11:59.019
WE'LL SHIMMY ON UP THERE
AND GRAB IT.
AND WHY THE MUSTACHES?

11:59.019 --> 12:02.022
WELL, YOU EVER SEEN A HARD HAT
WITHOUT A MUSTACHE UNDER IT?

12:02.022 --> 12:04.825
UH, NO, BUT IN MY DEFENSE,
I'M A SANE PERSON.

12:04.825 --> 12:08.398
GOTTA JAM. GOING OUT DANCING
WITH THE WIFE TONIGHT.
HEY. GO, ANDY.

12:08.398 --> 12:11.731
WE CAN'T GO DANCING.
I SENT THE NANNY HOME.

12:11.731 --> 12:13.363
I DON'T WANT HER.

12:13.363 --> 12:17.808
SO WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO DO,
GO SHAKE IT BY MYSELF?
THAT'S WHAT HE SAID.

12:17.808 --> 12:19.139
THAT WASN'T EVEN SUBTLE!

12:19.139 --> 12:22.212
TH-THERE'S AN ART TO THIS!

12:22.212 --> 12:23.743
(strumming chords)

12:23.743 --> 12:26.216
в™Є NO STRINGS ATTACHED,
NO NEED TO COMMIT в™Є

12:26.216 --> 12:28.448
в™Є WE'RE PALLIN' 'ROUND
WHILE WE'RE GETTIN' DOWN в™Є

12:28.448 --> 12:31.021
в™Є WE'RE FRIENDS WITH BENEFITS в™Є
в™Є FRIENDS WITH BENEFITS в™Є

12:31.021 --> 12:33.283
в™Є FRIENDS WITH BENEFITS в™Є

12:33.283 --> 12:34.885
HORRIBLE.

12:34.885 --> 12:37.828
WELL, YOU'LL BE
SINGING IT LATER.

12:37.828 --> 12:40.530
I HOPE NOT, BECAUSE IT'LL MEAN
SOMEONE HAS A GUN TO MY HEAD.
HEY, YOU WANT TO STAY
FOR COFFEE?

12:40.530 --> 12:44.264
EH, NOT TODAY.
OH, COOL.
SEE YOU ON THE FLIP SIDE.

12:44.264 --> 12:46.997
WHAT? PEOPLE STILL SAY
"FLIP SIDE."
(door opens and closes)

12:46.997 --> 12:49.099
SO HOW WAS THE BOOM-BOOM
LAST NIGHT?

12:49.099 --> 12:51.771
(scoffs) THAT IS SO MUCH WORSE
THAN "FLIP SIDE."

12:51.771 --> 12:54.905
I KNEW IT WHEN I SAID IT.
NO, WE ACTUALLY
DIDN'T EVEN HOOK UP.

12:54.905 --> 12:57.908
WE PLAYED PENNY CAN.
IT WAS SO MUCH FUN.

12:57.908 --> 13:00.050
OH, WE CAME UP
WITH THIS NEW TICKLE RULE.

13:00.050 --> 13:03.083
DID YOU?!
JULES, YOU ARE SO INTO HIM.

13:03.083 --> 13:05.285
ELLIE, I'VE GOT THIS
UNDER CONTROL.

13:05.285 --> 13:07.087
MM-HMM.

13:08.959 --> 13:10.390
LOOK AT HIM.

13:10.390 --> 13:12.893
LOOK AT HIM, JULES.

13:12.893 --> 13:15.225
I DON'T WANT TO.
I KNOW YOU DON'T.

13:15.225 --> 13:17.928
BECAUSE EVEN THOUGH
GRAYSON'S RIGHT OVER THERE...

13:17.928 --> 13:19.229
SAY IT, JULES.

13:21.001 --> 13:24.074
(voice breaks) IT'S LIKE
HE'S A MILLION MILES AWAY.

13:24.074 --> 13:26.877
(front door opens and closes)
MM-HMM.

13:33.914 --> 13:37.117
IS HE LOOKING AT ME?
WHAT ABOUT NOW? WHAT ABOUT NOW?
NO. NO. YEAH.

13:37.117 --> 13:39.419
REALLY?
NO.

13:39.419 --> 13:42.122
I JUST FEEL LIKE AN IDIOT.
I'M GONNA GO TALK TO HIM.
NO, BECAUSE YOU
CAN'T BE NORMAL.

13:42.122 --> 13:43.994
YES, I CAN.
HEY!

13:43.994 --> 13:46.826
YOU WORK THAT HOSE, BITCH!

13:46.826 --> 13:49.299
YOU'RE WEIRD, JULES.

13:49.299 --> 13:51.301
(chuckles)
WEIRD LIKE A FOX.

13:51.301 --> 13:53.303
OH, NO. PUT THE GUNS AWAY.

13:53.303 --> 13:55.135
DAMN THESE THINGS.
I HATE THEM!

14:01.141 --> 14:03.914
(whispering)
TRAV, CHECK IT OUT.

14:03.914 --> 14:07.147
(whispering) WHY ARE
WE WHISPERING?
BECAUSE THE BALLOON'S
RIGHT THERE.

14:07.147 --> 14:10.520
WE DON'T WANT TO SPOOK IT.
(normal voice) IT'S A BALLOON.

14:10.520 --> 14:14.154
(normal voice) NOW LOOK
WHAT YOU DID. COME ON!

14:15.525 --> 14:17.928
JUST TELL HIM
HOW YOU REALLY FEEL.

14:17.928 --> 14:21.191
BEING OPEN AND HONEST IS
A FIRM PLAN "C."

14:21.191 --> 14:23.393
PLEASE DON'T TELL ME
THE OTHER PLANS.

14:23.393 --> 14:25.395
PLAN "A" WOULD JUST BE

14:25.395 --> 14:27.537
CONTINUING ON WITH OUR FRIENDS
WITH BENEFITS THING FOREVER.

14:27.537 --> 14:30.300
PLAN "B" IS
A LITTLE MORE INTRICATE.

14:30.300 --> 14:32.572
FIRST, I HAVE TO MAKE HIM
FEEL INSECURE

14:32.572 --> 14:34.574
WITH A SERIES
OF INSULT-COMPLIMENTS,

14:34.574 --> 14:37.978
LIKE, UM, "I JUST LOVE
YOUR BEAUTIFUL, TINY EYES"

14:37.978 --> 14:39.980
OR, UM,
"YOUR RECEDING HAIRLINE

14:39.980 --> 14:43.053
REALLY MAKES
YOUR TINY EYES POP."

14:43.053 --> 14:45.485
SO YOU'RE GONNA FOCUS
ON THE EYES?

14:45.485 --> 14:47.187
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

14:47.187 --> 14:49.319
AND THEN TO STRIP WHAT'S LEFT
OF HIS SELF-ESTEEM,

14:49.319 --> 14:50.991
I'LL FATTEN HIM UP.

14:50.991 --> 14:53.663
NOW ONCE HE'S GAINED ABOUT
400 POUNDS AND HATES HIMSELF,

14:53.663 --> 14:55.996
THAT'S WHEN I CUT HIM LOOSE.

14:55.996 --> 14:59.169
THAT FAT BASTARD WILL BEG
TO HAVE ME BACK.

14:59.169 --> 15:01.271
EITHER I'LL WANT HIM
OR I WON'T,

15:01.271 --> 15:03.433
BUT THE POINT IS,
IT'LL BE MY CHOICE.

15:03.433 --> 15:07.107
WELL, I MEAN, I-I-IT SOUNDS LIKE
YOU HAVE A LOT OF OPTIONS.

15:07.107 --> 15:08.238
LOTS.

15:08.238 --> 15:11.481
NOT CRAZY AT ALL.
GOD, NO.

15:11.481 --> 15:13.984
HEY, ANDY.

15:13.984 --> 15:15.585
YOUR NOSTRILS LOOK
REALLY MAD.

15:15.585 --> 15:18.448
STOP TORTURING ELLIE
ABOUT THE NANNY.

15:18.448 --> 15:21.421
LOOK, THE BEST THING TO DO
WHEN SOMEONE PICKS ON YOU IS

15:21.421 --> 15:23.423
TO GIVE THEM A TASTE
OF THEIR OWN MEDICINE.

15:23.423 --> 15:26.426
I READ THAT IN A MAGAZINE. AND I
KNOW WHAT YOU'RE GONNA SAY,

15:26.426 --> 15:28.428
BUT I REALLY DID READ IT
IN A MAGAZINE.

15:28.428 --> 15:31.331
I SWEAR ON MY MOTHER'S LIFE.
WHAT MAGAZINE?

15:31.331 --> 15:34.334
WHAT KIND OF A FRIEND
WOULDN'T LET THAT SLIDE?

15:34.334 --> 15:37.237
NOW MY MOM IS GONNA DIE,
YOU MURDERER.

15:37.237 --> 15:39.239
DO YOU KNOW HOW HARD IT IS

15:39.239 --> 15:41.241
FOR A MAN
TO FIND A GIFT FOR HIS WIFE

15:41.241 --> 15:44.274
THAT SHE THINKS IS FOR HER
BUT IS ACTUALLY FOR HIM?

15:44.274 --> 15:46.316
LINGERIE DIDN'T WORK.
SHE SAW RIGHT THROUGH THAT.

15:46.316 --> 15:49.319
ORAL SEX CLASS?
HA HA. HUGE MISTAKE,

15:49.319 --> 15:51.651
AND AS IT TURNS OUT,
REALLY INSULTING.

15:51.651 --> 15:55.225
BUT THE NANNY? ELLIE SEES
THAT AS TOTALLY SELFLESS,

15:55.225 --> 15:58.228
BUT TO ME IT MEANS BEING ABLE
TO GO OUT TO A DINNER OR A MOVIE

15:58.228 --> 16:00.230
OR EVEN DANCING
ONCE IN A WHILE.

16:00.230 --> 16:02.462
DO YOU KNOW WHEN THE LAST TIME
I WENT DANCING WAS, LAURIE?

16:02.462 --> 16:04.334
HUH? DO YA?
NO!

16:04.334 --> 16:05.635
THIS...

16:05.635 --> 16:08.238
WAS STILL FRESH.

16:11.201 --> 16:13.273
HOW LONG ARE YOU GONNA
KEEP DOING THAT?

16:19.509 --> 16:22.082
(horn honking)
COME BACK!

16:22.082 --> 16:24.214
DAD, IT WON'T LISTEN!
IT'S JUST A BALLOON!

16:24.214 --> 16:27.317
(horns honk, tires screech)

16:27.317 --> 16:29.689
I'M GONNA GET YOU, BABY!
I'M GONNA GET YOU!

16:29.689 --> 16:31.721
AAH!

16:31.721 --> 16:33.663
DAD!

16:33.663 --> 16:36.596
DAD?

16:36.596 --> 16:38.198
OH, THANK GOD.

16:38.198 --> 16:40.200
(laughs)

16:40.200 --> 16:43.373
WAIT. DID YOU KNOW THERE WAS
ANOTHER LEDGE HERE?

16:43.373 --> 16:46.376
NO. I MAY HAVE GOT A LITTLE
CAUGHT UP IN THE MOMENT.

16:46.376 --> 16:47.377
(grunts)

16:47.377 --> 16:49.509
YOU ALMOST DIED!
AND FOR WHAT?

16:49.509 --> 16:53.183
TO GET YOUR DUMB BOAT
BACK IN THE WATER?

16:53.183 --> 16:57.117
LOOK, NO MORE DRIVING
SENIOR CITIZENS AROUND FOR CASH,

16:57.117 --> 16:58.748
NO MORE SLEEPING ON BENCHES.

16:58.748 --> 17:01.020
JUST NO MORE, OKAY?

17:03.593 --> 17:06.156
(scoffs) GROW UP, DAD.

17:06.156 --> 17:09.359
COME ON. HOW COULD
YOU NOT LAUGH AT THAT?

17:09.359 --> 17:12.162
HEY, STUDLY.
HEY. WHAT'S UP?

17:12.162 --> 17:14.164
YOU KNOW I-I WAS
JUST THINKING ABOUT

17:14.164 --> 17:16.336
HOW WE GET TO KEEP KNOCKING IT
OUT AND HIGH-FIVING AFTERWARDS

17:16.336 --> 17:18.208
UNTIL WE DIE.

17:18.208 --> 17:19.669
I'M SO PSYCHED.

17:19.669 --> 17:22.512
YOU JUST SAY, "SHALL WE?"

17:22.512 --> 17:25.275
NO PROBLEM. SHALL WE?

17:25.275 --> 17:26.816
в™Єв™Є

17:26.816 --> 17:28.818
GRAYSON, I CAN'T DO THIS.

17:28.818 --> 17:31.421
NO, THAT'S, UM,
THAT'S WHERE YOU SAY "INDEED."

17:31.421 --> 17:33.723
I JUST--I WANT MORE. I DO.

17:33.723 --> 17:36.726
I KNOW WHAT I SAID BEFORE,
BUT THAT WAS, LIKE,

17:36.726 --> 17:39.229
18 HOURS AGO,
AND THAT WAS THE OLD JULES.

17:39.229 --> 17:42.132
THE NEW JULES--
SHE SHOOTS FROM THE HIP.

17:42.132 --> 17:43.793
GO AWAY.

17:43.793 --> 17:47.767
LOOK, THE ONLY REASON
THAT YOU AND I DIDN'T DIVE IN

17:47.767 --> 17:49.599
IS BECAUSE WE'RE SCARED.

17:49.599 --> 17:52.302
I'VE BEEN MAKING
SO MANY DECISIONS MY WHOLE LIFE

17:52.302 --> 17:53.603
OUT OF FEAR.

17:53.603 --> 17:55.775
I JUST DON'T WANT
TO DO IT ANYMORE.

17:55.775 --> 17:59.309
COME ON. WE LIKE EACH OTHER.

17:59.309 --> 18:02.382
LET'S DO THIS.
LET'S DO THIS.

18:02.382 --> 18:04.854
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU WANT ME TO SAY.

18:04.854 --> 18:07.817
JUST SAY...

18:07.817 --> 18:09.759
"WHY NOT?"

18:09.759 --> 18:11.791
(Goldhawks) в™Є EACH NIGHT
WE'D FALL IN LOVE в™Є

18:11.791 --> 18:14.364
SO HOW'D IT GO?

18:14.364 --> 18:16.366
TOO SOON?

18:16.366 --> 18:18.468
JUST GIVE HIM SOME TIME.

18:18.468 --> 18:22.402
HE PROBABLY JUST THINKS THIS
ISN'T WHAT HE SIGNED UP FOR.
THAT'S WHAT HE SAID.

18:22.402 --> 18:24.604
I DON'T GET IT.

18:24.604 --> 18:27.337
NO, THAT'S ACTUALLY
WHAT HE SAID.
OOH.

18:27.337 --> 18:31.341
в™Є ..TO HOLD TO GET ME THROUGH
THE STAGE OF LIFE в™Є

18:31.341 --> 18:33.883
WELL, THAT'S TWICE
I'VE FOUND YOU IN HERE.

18:33.883 --> 18:36.216
I'M BUYING BEAR SPRAY.

18:36.216 --> 18:40.350
I WAS JUST TEASING
ABOUT THE NANNY, YOU WUSS.

18:40.350 --> 18:42.392
LOOK...

18:42.392 --> 18:45.555
I WANT TO TELL YOU SOMETHING,

18:45.555 --> 18:47.557
BUT YOU CAN'T TELL JULES.

18:47.557 --> 18:49.259
I'M INTRIGUED.

18:49.259 --> 18:51.761
YOU'RE KIND OF MY HERO.

18:51.761 --> 18:53.263
NO, THANK YOU.

18:53.263 --> 18:55.205
OKAY, NOT YOU PERSONALLY,

18:55.205 --> 18:58.338
BUT YOU HAVE EVERYTHING--

18:58.338 --> 19:00.870
A GREAT HOUSE, GREAT FAMILY,

19:00.870 --> 19:03.313
FANCY OLD LADY CLOTHES.

19:03.313 --> 19:05.645
THE DIRTY SECRET IS,

19:05.645 --> 19:08.248
I WANT YOUR LIFE, NOT JULES'.

19:08.248 --> 19:10.250
SHE WORKS LIKE A DOG.

19:10.250 --> 19:12.422
AND I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.
IF I DO MARRY SMITH,

19:12.422 --> 19:14.924
JULES IS GONNA WALK
INTO THE OFFICE ONE DAY,

19:14.924 --> 19:16.826
LOOK OVER AT MY CHAIR,

19:16.826 --> 19:19.359
AND THERE'S JUST
GONNA BE A PUFF OF SMOKE.

19:19.359 --> 19:21.331
AND WHEN I HAVE A BABY,

19:21.331 --> 19:23.333
I'M GONNA HIRE, LIKE,
A 5-PERSON PARENTING TEAM

19:23.333 --> 19:26.165
WHO'LL WEAR UNIFORMS
I DESIGN.

19:26.165 --> 19:28.838
в™Є WE'VE GOTTA KEEP THIS FIRE,
WE'VE GOTTA KEEP THIS FIRE в™Є

19:28.838 --> 19:31.371
ARE YOU TRYING TO SAY,
"THANK YOU"?

19:31.371 --> 19:32.672
в™Є WE'VE GOTTA KEEP THIS FIRE в™Є

19:32.672 --> 19:34.774
YOU'RE WELCOME.

19:34.774 --> 19:36.276
GET DRESSED, WOMAN!

19:36.276 --> 19:38.408
WHOO-HOO! WE'RE GOING OUT!

19:38.408 --> 19:39.649
(laughs)

19:39.649 --> 19:42.352
LET'S GO GET SOME DINNER.
SURE. WHY NOT?

19:42.352 --> 19:43.853
GREAT. SHALL WE?

19:43.853 --> 19:46.456
(door opens)
CAN YOU ASK ME ANOTHER WAY?

19:46.456 --> 19:47.587
(door closes)
WHAT?

19:47.587 --> 19:49.719
HELLO. I'LL GO, TOO,

19:49.719 --> 19:51.591
IF YOU'RE DRIVING.

19:51.591 --> 19:53.793
в™Є I CAN TELL YOU'VE GOT ... в™Є

19:53.793 --> 19:56.326
NO WAY!

19:56.326 --> 19:59.329
I KNOW I'VE BEEN TOO BROKE TO DO
AS MUCH FOR YOU AS YOUR MOM,

19:59.329 --> 20:02.332
BUT I DIDN'T WANT YOU TO GO OFF
TO COLLEGE WITHOUT A CAR.

20:02.332 --> 20:04.334
NOW IF WE HAD GOTTEN
THAT DAMN BALLOON,

20:04.334 --> 20:06.506
I COULD HAVE GIVEN HER
A NEW PAINT JOB

20:06.506 --> 20:08.938
AND FIXED THOSE BULLET HOLES.
THIS IS ALL YOUR DAD'S DOING.

20:08.938 --> 20:12.242
HE'S BEEN WORKING EXTRA JOBS
FOR MONTHS.
MAN, NOW I FEEL LIKE A TOOL.

20:12.242 --> 20:14.244
I KNOW. IT MAKES IT
EVEN MORE DELICIOUS.

20:14.244 --> 20:16.846
NOW YOU WANT TO TAKE
THIS PANTY DROPPER FOR A SPIN?

20:16.846 --> 20:18.918
YEAH, BUT I WANT ONE THING.

20:18.918 --> 20:22.522
WHOO!
WHOO-HOO-HOO-HOO!

20:22.522 --> 20:24.324
(tires peal)

20:24.324 --> 20:26.296
в™Є OH в™Є

20:26.296 --> 20:29.399
в™Є WE'VE GOTTA KEEP THIS FIRE в™Є

20:29.399 --> 20:30.400
в™Є WE'VE GOTTA KEEP THIS FIRE в™Є

20:30.400 --> 20:32.532
HEY.

20:32.532 --> 20:35.265
в™Є WE'VE GOTTA KEEP THIS FIRE в™Є

20:35.265 --> 20:36.566
в™Є BURNING в™Є

20:36.566 --> 20:39.008
WHY DID YOU DO THAT?

20:39.008 --> 20:40.270
WHY NOT?

20:40.270 --> 20:42.972
в™Є KEEP BURNING, KEEP BURNING в™Є

20:42.972 --> 20:45.915
в™Є YEAH, KEEP BURNING в™Є

20:45.915 --> 20:47.777
в™Є KEEP BURNING в™Є

20:47.777 --> 20:51.381
в™Є KEEP BURNING, YEAH в™Є

20:51.381 --> 20:56.255
в™Є WE'VE GOTTA KEEP THIS FIRE,
KEEP BURNING в™Є

21:02.932 --> 21:05.264
THANKS FOR GETTING ME
THE MUSTACHE, GUYS.

21:05.264 --> 21:07.397
I HAVEN'T HAD ONE
SINCE EIGHTH GRADE.

21:07.397 --> 21:10.370
YOU LOOK LIKE DOM DeLUISE
AND BURT REYNOLDS' LOVE CHILD.

21:10.370 --> 21:13.443
HA HA.
(laughs) HEY,
I GOT A GREAT IDEA.

21:13.443 --> 21:15.945
I SAY WE MAKE A MAN PACT
AND WEAR THESE FOR A MONTH.

21:15.945 --> 21:17.947
I MEAN, I WOULDN'T CALL THAT
A "GREAT" IDEA,

21:17.947 --> 21:20.950
BUT HEY, WHY NOT? I'M DOWN.
WELL, I'LL GIVE IT A SHOT,
FELLAS,

21:20.950 --> 21:23.953
BUT ONCE ELLIE SEES THIS,
SHE'S GONNA MAKE ME TAKE IT OFF.

21:23.953 --> 21:26.055
SHE LOVES THIS FACE TOO MUCH.

21:27.757 --> 21:29.759
WHAT'S THAT ON YOUR FACE?

21:29.759 --> 21:32.762
WHAT IS THIS THING ON MY FACE?
I'VE HAD IT ON FOR A WEEK!

21:32.762 --> 21:35.725
A WEEK! SERIOUSLY?

21:35.725 --> 21:37.327
CALM DOWN.
